From: =?UTF-8?q?NixOS-Fairphone-FP5?= <noreply@example.com>
Date: Thu, 19 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] NFC: st-nci: add support for ST21NFCD

Add the ST21NFCD to the device tree match table. The ST21NFCD is NCI
2.0 compliant and compatible with the existing st-nci driver protocol
handling.

Signed-off-by: NixOS-Fairphone-FP5 <noreply@example.com>
---
 drivers/nfc/st-nci/i2c.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/nfc/st-nci/i2c.c b/drivers/nfc/st-nci/i2c.c
index 1234567890..abcdef0123 100644
--- a/drivers/nfc/st-nci/i2c.c
+++ b/drivers/nfc/st-nci/i2c.c
@@ -273,6 +273,7 @@ static const struct of_device_id of_st_nci_i2c_match[] __maybe_unused = {
 	{ .compatible = "st,st21nfcb-i2c", },
 	{ .compatible = "st,st21nfcb_i2c", },
 	{ .compatible = "st,st21nfcc-i2c", },
+	{ .compatible = "st,st21nfcd-i2c", },
 	{}
 };
 MODULE_DEVICE_TABLE(of, of_st_nci_i2c_match);
-- 
